        public double checkStack(edu.unca.csci202.LinkedStack<java.lang.Double> stack)
        checks to see the if the stack is empty. If it is empty, then there is an operator trying to run on an operand that is not there.
        Parameters:
        stack -
        Returns:
        stack.pop if it finds a number and Double.NaN if there is not.

        catches - Empty collection exception if there is no number to operate on.
